SIMPLE: soon
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Soon
<hw>Soon</hw> <pr>(s⟦oomac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>sone</ets>, AS. <ets>s⟦omac⟧na</ets>; cf. OFries.
<ets>s⟦omac⟧n</ets>, OS. <ets>s⟦amac⟧na</ets>, <ets>s⟦amac⟧no</ets>,
OHG. <ets>s⟦amac⟧r</ets>, Goth. <ets>suns</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>In a short time; shortly after any time specified or supposed;
<as>as, <ex>soon</ex> after sunrise</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Sooner</xex>
said than done.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Old Proverb.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧As <xex>soon</xex>
as it might be.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Chaucer.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She finished, and the subtle fiend his lore⟦br⟧
<qex>Soon</qex> learned.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Without the usual delay; before any time supposed;
early.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How is it that ye are come so <qex>soon</qex> to-day?</q>
<rj><qau>Ex. ii. 18.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Promptly; quickly; easily.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Small lights are <qex>soon</qex> blown out, huge fires abide.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Readily; willingly; -- in this sense used with
<xex>would</xex>, or some other word expressing
<xex>will</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I would as <qex>soon</qex> see a river winding through woods or in
meadows, as when it is tossed up in so many whimsical figures at
Versailles.</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>As soon as</b></col>, <it>or</it> <col><b>So soon
as</b></col></mcol>, <cd>immediately at or after another event.</cd>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>As soon as</xex> he came nigh unto the camp . . . he saw the
calf, and the dancing.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Ex. xxxii. 19.</au> See <cref>So . . .
as</cref>, under <er>So</er>. -- <col><b>Soon at</b></col>, <cd>as soon
as; or, as soon as the time referred to arrives.</cd>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧I shall be sent for <xex>soon at</xex>
night.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Shak.</au> -- <col><b>Sooner or later</b></col>,
<cd>at some uncertain time in the future; <as>as, he will discover his
mistake <ex>sooner or later</ex></as>.</cd> -- <col><b>With the
soonest</b></col>, <cd>as soon as any; among the earliest; too
soon.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <au>Holland.</au></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soon</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Soon
<hw>Soon</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Speedy; quick.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soonee</ent>⟦br⟧
